5. Conclusions
The cooperation between the two accounting offices has proved its worth.
Thus, necessary knowledge of the systems used in both countries could be obtained: This concerns in particular: • Intra-Community transactions, • Risk management at the UST, in particular with regard to the selection of dumped transactions, • Recovery of UST claims and • UST audit of large enterprises.
The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting USt fraud and in the systems described above.
These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.
They can also be used to initiate a discussion with interested bodies on what audit approaches and anti-fraud strategies can be used. This applies, for example. For example, the relationship between Member States and the EU Commission.
The experience and knowledge gained should encourage US management to continue to be examined together.
